The paper deals with cross-modal retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) tasks. The proposed approach involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of machine learning (LG). The paper also mentions the use of semantic information, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (CL). Finally, the experiments involve image and text datasets, which are commonly used in the sub-category of multimedia (MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.IR, and cs.LG, followed by cs.MM and cs.CL.
